<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="O" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Oerswell" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">O'erswell,</orth> 1) intr. to rise above the banks: <cit><quote>let floods o.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 97</bibl></cit> (Pistol's speech). 2) trans. to overflow: <cit><quote>o. thy shores,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.337" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 337</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>till the wine o. the cup,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 4.3.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 3, 161</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>